IN line with the State Smart City Initiative and address UN sustainable development goals whilst fulfilling the Traffic and Transportation aspect of the Lagos State Govt’s THEMES Agenda, the state has flagged off Lagos Bike Share Scheme. Speaking at the launching of the Pilot Scheme of AWABIKE organised by Office of Public Private Partnership (PPP) and held at Carpark, Adeyemi Bero Hall, Alausa, Ikeja. The Director General, PPP, Ope George said the scheme will promote environmental stability while enhancing economic opportunities for the benefit of the state. “The scheme is a service in which bicycles are made available for shared use to individuals on a short term basis for a token fee without incurring the costs and responsibilities associated with ownership.”